Prerequisite : git should be installed
Check by running 
git --version
***/

Step 1

Create a remote repository on http://github.com/username/

Login -> Repositories -> New -> Enter name(XXX) -> Make public/private -> Save

Step 2

Prepare local repository on your machine

using command line -> cd to root of your project(to be pushed)
-> do 'git init'
-> do 'git add .'
-> do 'git commit'

Step 3

Connect to your remote repository from your machine

continue on the command line 
-> do 'git remote add ANY_NAME(YYY) http://github.com/username/XXX-repo.git' [*DONT FORGET THE EXTENSION]
Check if the remote has been successfully connected
-> do 'git remote -v'
YOU WILL SEE SOMETHING LIKE THIS IF CONNECTED SUCCESSFULLY
[ http://xxxxxxxx/ (fetch)
  http://xxxxxxxx/ (push)
]

Step 4

Sync the remote repo with the local repo

-> do 'git fetch YYY'
-> do 'git pull YYY master'

Step 5

Push your local repo to the remote repo

-> do 'git push YYY'

ENTER USERNAME AND PASSWORD WHEN PROMPTED
DONE

Step 6

Check my going to http://github.com/username/XXX/
YOUR REPOSITORY IS UPDATED

